[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering class loading**\n\nI'm thinking about using Class.forName with an unknown name in native code, and how it might interact with a custom loader. If the custom loadClass method can return an existing class, then it's quite possible that I wouldn’t need to define anything dynamically. It raises interesting questions about class management and how that impacts performance and behavior in different scenarios. Let me explore this further!\n\n**Examining class loading logic**\n\nI’m diving into class loading details, specifically how to override the `loadClass` method. The method `Class.forName(name, true, loader)` probably relies on `loadClass(name)` which is interesting. The public `loadClass` method calls `loadClass(name, false)`, and the VM might call `loadClass(String)`.\n\nI need to manage both public and protected versions of `loadClass`, which complicates things. I’m considering whether `resolveClass` should be called or if it could throw an error. There’s a lot to sort through!\n\n**Implementing class loading**\n\nI’m focusing on how to implement the `loadClass` method with an override. I plan to check if an alias exists in the `aliases` map, and return it if found; otherwise, I'll call the superclass's `loadClass`. \n\nThere could be a challenge with `Class.forName` not accepting an alias if it looks for an existing class with a different name, which could lead to test failures. I think I can create a test that ensures the proper exception is thrown if an alias isn’t found. That feels like a solid approach!\n\n**Considering coverage integration**\n\nI’m contemplating whether “add high coverage integration” would prefer that the tests succeed. Still, I can stick to the rules, which are supposed to be version-agnostic. This approach will account for overloaded `Class.forName`. I realize that if the first attempt fails, the second can still be executed, eliminating the need for a custom implementation. It feels good to keep things straightforward while ensuring coverage with these options!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c3f87fa662cfb580169f14f2d3e54819c8cf63b79a985e7bf\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8U9P36boz58bVP9N3Rb2EMXUK7vBPnRZpvUv6VO9Xyv66Iii7C1ArFkERn9iH0Tx0AMVeTc7k8yKzcKHGKolaFL7-EYxnOj9uU4aL21yyPwxiZCfjIuOSrNlX0YGg40RXYQ0AH_96RjQOUTlL_qLL_3912yVVuTtsIr6MEbXI30-XufEtVzH44t40KMzDpLh13y4bYPfXzwQSSywTvB9IzeAUVYffcawOD5uYWMR5hrlRpTcz9zxEIqTIETaTvvuRmw--dLQfsRU0KJhBdt7zBCROne1PkTPOu1OI2nHsr5V4CV0HFSd0pP0b5pVI6GtYc9oKGFDZ1ObwViaUvF0DocNKUwWsYd35ns1EyaoSBKS2peBbFHOzHSp4T9X0LMiTSwQoJMaHfeD8ZefcEzfLWUrkLDgvkQExl0dG7K2TnoKaNl9mJhE3V6Z7xGznxlNNDcikGV_RVJQn-Ah5MSyjugpsv1okvDpWcZ7yHay4OR-G2CnTIdDHm300D37qKkv0rq0_lRzQeZh2hSfDcR-reikiKbM76sLQfP3-f2Zqy9FN0dI4uNURiKXmdK5CAp6licWWJbYPS0ybnvko07OsirkF__cSwSq7jRUX-Ge4wwPTaSrQWdBwQtzbnJZRvNW79DTDa_KCWzWlLls3pdl-NTtxbzAJLgBTZlVkgiuvIE3TMpa7mWA5JT0vzd1f6pfrVj5BoIXugeTl4t5vLavlewE5jbEH-izU0HuxTg4GiZ1fKmmjhzcLZbast1bKfs6kqQa7fUhh0dvaqNI-8cg6Mj1sgq7TCL4uH0H3uDnu5nP6RRPp0HH8eVCa0_NLj6vUmhMOqk2u4O8qFLpSA8detr-8w4CxIuabi9zawbJpk2jtiSbpPWNLGBBe7hYhxyxjqN1l3syxXUb3PQ-hEHOZk5xjsIWdQMdHb9leL1IrGE1WDEJMho3vMoedgCgKmTx4cRAnMGSZv3a9P_1IJrcQGC4htdzG-wGupQd9xdJxxAc0GdAlV5b0KS6ZWuAm3uRnVP0FMiDZlJjLVTTJkhnZLdY3sYPI78YvXx2O3vX__qq4Wz-JVjdXlOFSax96W995XhnCjSSfvCG-Y40WWtJdl93Kbz9C27ARe1zbhqjTEBNcaoSbNuhUH3o0TT1heB_-t1e4LCbkCjNTxnaRQ3WGls538bvtORldNGLfwXphsmS9wgmaW6sEmRssLwOM2YXUj1rFM5aQQX2jQs33tcj0Ze_NZ9RMmm5nIM_XSsOtn9OSsplcWd-KHm5d9o4EDWcd1ATAIXo4uxYERBjtj_IrqB525gslp3-8dIrrbPRF6A5v7mp88k3WgUqhrdOOQFmaolTQOGjh9eFueq6d7O97PS6mzjPtdo3Rr0lzw6U7v2-FfznXorOaGqoWABPUOzzIBKP38ZBInbH_0l2ACZUkc7Of9DUuKD3p1of6hk0TE2KHL2b6X4jEdRB92XHOW361nS7NkQwTraKV-tKIWD1ZdWY79xPWyZEPoywfRFsu9h6e8e7apaOjXzcSEITb6FKxlsgDP8Xz42Ng6trPvVWpI3pW4cnfcdo4maYcBc8ZyFXFmNqzffuAGqbvUHWo2bgM79rdmxtuR0k1i-GgdH8B2X4EzEJnH9orREDC7hB09FNtGegBnQkvnnoMR9i-1Mnv3VNRREc5trClRyt8B7q4PJyl1-1lEIyGh4NHKYvX_kZCP